FBIS4-37710 "drnes121_j_94017" FBIS-NES-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Northern Plane Shot Down Northern Plane Shot Down LD2206171194 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1630 GMT 22 Jun 94 LD2206171194 Kuwait KUNA Arabic BFN [Text] Aden, 22 June, KUNA -- At noon today, southern antiaircraft defenses shot down a northern warplane that was raiding Aden. A southern military source has said that the aircraft was trying to raid the television station, which is situated in the mountainous al-Tawahi region. He added that the northern warplanes conducted more raids on Aden a few hours after the airport was the target of a Katyusha barrage from a northern military launcher. He pointed out that the shells did not hit the airport, but a number of ordinary houses were damaged instead. The source did not give any details on the damage of the missile barrage. KUNA's correspondent, however, saw a number of fire engines heading to the areas close to the airport, which is situated in the Khur Maksar district in the heart of the city of Aden.
